  "body": "The code display in the debugger is small enough for most uses, but sometimes it can be useful to know what is further up or further down in the code, so it would be nice if the display could be scrollable or there would be the possibility to enlarge the code view.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9073706/116675040-aea9e580-a9a5-11eb-9e75-512d32523313.png)\r\n\r\nAnother feature for the code view could be to display if a conditional jump will be taken or not, so that we already know in advance that we will jump in to steps. Maybe opcodes that will be executed soon could be highlighted, or there could be a line visualizing the control flow:\r\n\r\n![cf](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9073706/116676107-e1081280-a9a6-11eb-8046-be3b239fc0bd.png)\r\n",
